note: LAR D/ST surrendered the fewest passing yards and fantasy points to QBs last season. They'll open the season at home vs Andy Dalton, in Dalton's first start for his new team. Expect Aaron Donald and Leonard Floyd to get after him, with Jalen Ramsey shadowing the Bears' best receiver in Allen Robinson. This is a match made in heaven for the Rams defense, making it the top D/ST of the week.

There's no telling how the new-look Lions offense will look this season, but Jared Goff and Co. will get thrown into the fire right away in a tough matchup with San Fran's defense (one that has played him twice a year since he was drafted). SF D/ST is a no-brainer top-5 play in Week 1.

Justin Herbert is a force to be reckoned with, but Washington Football Team's defense is no joke. This unit could legitimately finish as the DST1 this season, and unless the matchup is against Patrick Mahomes or Josh Allen, they're shaping up to be a set-and-forget in 2021.

It may look like an unfavorable matchup on paper, but Miami's defense was very productive for fantasy managers a season ago finishing as the DST4. Mac Jones won the starting job in New England, but this will still be his first NFL start against a strong division rival. Don't count out Miami as a top-3 D/ST in Week 1.

The G-Men look like they might be a dumpster fire on offense yet again, but the defense has plenty of promise. Teddy Bridgewater should be an upgrade at QB, but he won't be lighting anyone up. NYG D/ST is a sneaky option for Week 1, playing at home against a QB in a new offense.
